Scheme Name: Swachh Bharat Mission – Urban 2.0

Details:
A sanitation scheme for the construction of Individual Household Latrines (IHHL) for urban households. The Mission has the following components:

 - Household toilets, including conversion of insanitary latrines into pour-flush latrines
 - Community toilets
 - Public toilets
 - Solid waste management
 - IEC & Public Awareness
 - Capacity building and Administrative & Office Expenses (A&OE)

Benefits:
Financial support for toilet construction:

 - ₹6667 (in Andhra Pradesh, Bihar, Chhattisgarh, Goa, Gujarat, Haryana, Jharkhand, Karnataka, Kerala, Madhya Pradesh, Maharashtra, Odisha, Punjab, Rajasthan, Tamil Nadu, Telangana, Uttar Pradesh, West Bengal)

 - ₹12,000 (in Uttarakhand, Himachal Pradesh, Arunachal Pradesh, Manipur, Meghalaya, Mizoram, Nagaland, Sikkim, Tripura, Assam)

 - ₹5333 (in Union Territories)

Eligibility:
Any urban household that:

 - Does not have access to an individual household toilet
 - Has an insanitary toilet
 - 80% of urban households engaging in open defecation are eligible

Application Process:
Online:

 - Register on IHHL portal using Name, Mobile Number, Email, Address, ID Type, and ID Number.

 - After login, fill in:

    Geographical Details: State, District, ULB Name, Ward No.
    Toilet Owner’s Details: Name, Gender, Father/Husband’s Name, Mobile Number, Address, Status of Existing Toilet, Aadhaar number, Bank Account details, and Photograph.

 - After submission, an acknowledgment slip with Application ID and bank details is generated.

Documents Required:

 - Aadhaar Linked Transfer of Incentive
 - Aadhaar Number
 - Bank Passbook
 - Passport-sized Photograph